messageBody:
It's handwritten Hebrew. Handwritten Hebrew looks very
different from printed Hebrew, and interestingly, some of
the handwritten letter shapes do resemble Quikscript.

Gary Yu

Alexander Lampros wrote:

>Go take a look at this link:
>http://www.nytimes.com/2004/08/16/arts/music/16bump.html
>
>The guy is holding up what sure looks like some sort
>of quickscript. I realize its an Article about
>Israel, but it doesn't look like Hebrew. Can anyone
>more experienced than I read it?
>
>Yours,
>
>Alex
>
>
